name: Nick Anderson
description: After months of political theater, a 43-day government shutdown, and endless speeches about “standing with working families,” Senate Republicans finished the year by doing exactly what they set out to do: blocking the renewal of Affordable Care Act subsidies and guaranteeing that millions of Americans will see their premiums skyrocket on January 1. This wasn’t an accident or a breakdown in negotiations. It was a deliberate choice, made by the same party that insists it understands “the struggles of ordinary Americans.”
title: Affordable Care Act

name: Pedro X. Molina
description: The “peace” prize commissioned by FIFA and tailored to Trump's liking has been the subject of worldwide ridicule. And it's not just because FIFA, an organization better known internationally for its corruption and manipulation of a sport that, incidentally, causes the most division and violence around the world, has no experience or authority in terms of peace, but also because the recipient doesn't either.
title: Trump's "peace" prize
